  "response_text": "A bright, cozy living room is set up for a home assembly project. Two young adults kneel on a white shag rug around a low white coffee table with pale wooden legs. The man, on the left, wears a brown jacket and dark pants; the woman, on the right, wears a dark blue button-up shirt and a colorful headband holding back curly dark hair. Behind them are large sunlit windows, a brick wall, a tan sofa with a yellow blanket, cardboard boxes, framed pictures leaning against the wall, and small tools scattered on the rug. They are looking at the table and the instruction papers, as if finishing the build.\n\nThe woman studies a large folded instruction sheet while holding a small white part in one hand. The man, still kneeling, reaches toward the table. A purple drink can sits on the glossy white tabletop. As he adjusts or moves the table, the surface tilts sharply, and the can begins to slide across it. A close view shows the purple can tipped on its side on the white tabletop, its open pull tab visible.\n\nThe woman reacts with alarm. She faces forward with her mouth open wide, eyes enlarged, one hand raised like a stop signal and the instruction paper flying upward beside her. The paper lands on the rug, where the printed page is visible with the bold heading “Instructions,” small diagrams of the table, and a simple cartoon-like figure holding tools. A pinkish-purple streak of spilled liquid appears on the tabletop nearby.\n\nA roll of Bounty paper towels is quickly placed upright on the white table by an arm in a rolled-up blue sleeve. The roll has a bright green label with the large “Bounty” logo and the phrase “The Quicker Picker Upper” printed beneath it. The spill remains visible as a long pink-purple smear on the tabletop to the right of the roll.\n\nA hand presses a folded white Bounty paper towel onto the purple spill. The towel is thick and bright white, and the hand smooths it firmly across the glossy surface. As the towel moves over the liquid, the purple streak shortens and lightens, being drawn into the towel. Small disclaimer text appears near the bottom of the image. Large white-and-purple on-screen words build over the cleaned surface: “absorbs like a sponge,” with “sponge” shown in large purple letters. By the time the towel lifts away, the tabletop underneath looks clean, while the towel has absorbed the purple liquid.\n\nThe commercial then shows a side-by-side comparison on a plain white surface. On the left, a hand uses a sheet labeled by nearby on-screen text as the “Leading Ordinary Brand”; on the right, another hand uses a Bounty towel, with the Bounty logo displayed near the lower right. Both hands press towels into separate purple puddles. The ordinary-brand sheet on the left becomes heavily soaked and dark purple, and when it is lifted, a visible drop of purple liquid falls back down, leaving liquid behind. On the right, the Bounty towel also turns purple where it has absorbed the spill, but it is handled in a thicker folded pad and continues wiping the surface. The Bounty side shows the hand sweeping the towel across the remaining small pink puddle until the surface looks clear. Fine print along the bottom mentions flavored sparkling water and indicates a time-lapse comparison.\n\nThe final scene shifts to a clean, softly lit kitchen-like counter. A bright green spill lies spread across the white surface in the foreground. A roll of Bounty drops down upright directly onto the green liquid, standing in the middle of the puddle. Its white roll and green Bounty label face forward, with the “Bounty” name and “The Quicker Picker Upper” slogan visible. A small blue P&G logo appears in the upper right corner as the roll sits on the spill, surrounded by the vivid green liquid.",
